# Human prose & no agent traces

Write like a maintainer of this exchange matching engine — not like a chat assistant.

## Never commit

- Mentions of Cursor, Copilot, Claude, ChatGPT, “agent”, “agentic workers”, or skill names (`superpowers:*`)
- Boilerplate: “As an AI…”, “Hope this helps”, emoji decoration, filler summaries
- Plan banners that instruct AI agents how to run the plan
- Paths under `docs/superpowers/` (use `docs/specs/`, `docs/plans/`)

## Comments & docs

- Prefer short why/intent over restating the code
- Name real constraints (Java parity, MQ topic shape, restore path) instead of ticket slogans
- Tables may use plain Yes/No or status words; avoid decorative emoji spam in new text

## Code style

- Match neighboring modules: naming, error strings, log fields, test assert messages
- Dual-track: default production path stays `match-core`; `hp-engine` stays opt-in
- Do not invent branding, fake vendors, or placeholder company names

## Before finishing a change

Scan the diff for the strings above and for assistant-style hedging. Rewrite until it reads as ordinary engineering notes.
